content.text:
# Reliable Subscription & Customer Automation with Chargebee ...
created: 2025-12-22, last updated: 2026-05-27, [Read more](https://www.chargebee.com/tutorials/reliable-subscription-customer-automation-with-chargebee-webhooks-and-the-hookdeck-event-gateway/)

The Source provides the webhook URL that Chargebee will send events to.
It also configures authentication to validate the source of the webhook requests.
You can obtain the API key for your Hookdeck account in the Secrets page under Settings.
```
const sourceResponse = await fetch(
"https://api.hookdeck.com/2025-07-01/sources",
{
method: "PUT",
headers: {
Authorization: `Bearer ${HOOKDECK_API_KEY}`,
"Content-Type": "application/json",
},
body: JSON.stringify({
name: "chargebee",
type: "CHARGEBEE_BILLING",
config: {
auth: {
username: process.env.CHARGEBEE_WEBHOOK_USERNAME,
password: process.env.CHARGEBEE_WEBHOOK_PASSWORD,
},
},
}),
},
);
const source = await sourceResponse.json();
const hookdeckSourceUrl = source.url;
...
```
...
The Basic Auth credentials must match those configured in the Source, or requests will fail authentication.
...
The authentication middleware verifies both the Hookdeck webhook signature and Chargebee's Basic Auth credentials.
This ensures that requests come from the Event Gateway and originated from Chargebee.

